TASK 1

Defines a function factorial(n) → calculates the factorial of a number n using recursion.
Takes user input (a) → asks the user to enter a number.
Prints the result → displays the factorial of the entered number.

TASK 2

Takes user input (a) → asks the user to enter a number.
Imports the math module → to use mathematical functions.
Calculates and prints:
The square root of a → math.sqrt(a)
The natural logarithm of a → math.log(a)
The sine of a (in radians) → math.sin(a)
